TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
For \(\sin 2x+\cos x =0, \)
use a double-angle or half-angle formula to simplify the equation and then 
find all solutions of the equation
in the interval \( [0,2\pi). \)
$BR
The answer is  \( x = \)  \{ans_rule(35)\}.
$BR
$BBOLD Note: $EBOLD If there is more than one solution enter them separated by commas.
If needed enter \( \pi \) as pi. 
$BR
EOT

$ans1= $PI/2;
$ans2= 7*$PI/6;
$ans3= 3*$PI/2;
$ans4= 11*$PI/6;

&ANS(number_list_cmp("$ans1,$ans2,$ans3,$ans4"));

